    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-10-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-01-09T16:18:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Directs the Administrator of the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) to issue an order to require: (1) the installation of secondary barriers to prevent access to the flight deck of a commercial aircraft; (2) with respect to an aircraft that is equipped with a cockpit door, such secondary barriers remain locked while the aircraft is in flight and the cockpit door separating the flight deck and the passenger area is open; and (3) with respect to an aircraft that is not equipped with a cockpit door, such secondary barriers remain locked as determined by the pilot.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To direct the Administrator of the Federal Aviation Administration to issue an order regarding secondary cockpit barriers.</title>
